<br>
Now I know that there will be post about how the groups were not set up before the raid and How this was WAY to many people to go to hate. However we must bare in mind the fact that when this raid was posted we were going to fear. When a raid location has to changed so close to raid day It does make it a lot harder, not to mention the time involved, to set things up in advance. Please keep that in mind when posting to this thread.<br>
<br>
I saw a RL trying very hard to keep things under control, without upsetting anyone. I saw at the same time other members trying to help maintain order. Considering all that was going on, not a bad job either, I might add. My reasons for not leading raids was supported by what I saw. I can't be assertive. Either I'm passive or aggressive.<br>
<br>
I believe the problems we had had a lot more to do with people not knowing why they were being asked what they were being asked to do as to not paying attention. Every raid has unique procedures but certain things are always the same. ie always wait for the MT to call engage. Why? Not just so every one is on the same mob but also so the MT has a chance to get on the right mob and this way he/she can retarget if he/she needs to. NEVER ASSUME that the target of the MT before he/she calls engage is the same one after it's called. Shut off auto attack on assist. I believe this caused more mez breaks than people not assisting.<br>
<br>
Another point, TOO MANY channels. When we have people without PoP, they DO NOT see raid chat. So it shouldn't be used.<br>
<br>
Last point in our guilds it is just as important to teach our members, without raid XP, the proper procedures and different rules for raids, as it is to get them involved with Fed raids.<br>
<br>
In closing FUN FUN FUN. This is what raids should be. This one became fun when people finally understood what was expected of them. If they know it before the raid the FUN can start at the beginning as well.<br>
<br>
Damn I talk to much.<br>
<br>
Looking forward to your next raid Lov<br>
Judge<br>
