<br>
I do have some areas i would like to address for future reference.  <br>
<br>
One.  PoP vs non PoP.  I believe that we had one non PoP group.  This ment that the PoP raid channel would not be heard by all.  This needs to be addressed in one of several ways.  Inform everyone at sign up that they need pop to participate.  This would ensure that everyone can see the raid channel.  Alternately, to include our brothers and sisters that dont have PoP, let everyone know that we will be using the channel designated on the sign up and not the raid channel.  Either way would solve the communication problem.<br>
<br>
Two.  I have found it useful to go ahead and post groups for raids even if circumstances change.  This at the very least provides a framework for the raid and gives people a feeling of some organization.  It helps to reduce the number of paniced tells and the static in chat channels.  This in turn makes your job easier as raid leader.  <br>
<br>
Three.  You did an excellent job of designating the main cleric/enchanter/shammy for buffs.  Hehe One of the secrets of leadership is to find good people who know how to do their jobs and to let them do it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Those are my suggestions/observations for this raid.  Again thank you for sponcering it.<br>
<br>
VonAlbrecht Jaeger<br>
Guildleader Souls of Defiance <br>
Officer of the Federation<br>
